    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dutch variations of Art Nouveau that stress form based on function, construction and material. Characteristics are a division of constructive and functional elements, respect for the material used, and restricted use of ornament that accentuates form. This style flourished in Amsterdam. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
